=== Remark ===

A Banach space formula_1 is reflexive if it is linearly isometric to its bidual under this canonical embedding formula_76 James&#x27; space is an example of a non-reflexive space which is linearly isometric to its bidual. Furthermore, the image of James&#x27; space under the canonical embedding formula_62 has codimension one in its bidual.

A Banach space formula_1 is called quasi-reflexive (of order formula_79) if the quotient formula_80 has finite dimension formula_81

=== Examples ===

# Every finite-dimensional normed space is reflexive, simply because in this case, the space, its dual and bidual all have the same linear dimension, hence the linear injection formula_62 from the definition is bijective, by the rank–nullity theorem.
